{"title_page": "Andie Chen", "text_new": "{{short description|Singaporean actor, host and vlogger|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{use dmy dates}}\n{{infobox person\n| name = Andie Chen\n| image = \n| alt = \n| caption = \n| birth_name = Andy Tan Bang Jun\n| birth_date = \n| birth_place = [[Singapore]]\n| residence = [[Singapore]]\n| nationality = [[Singaporean]]\n| education = [[Tanglin Secondary School]] \n| alma_mater = [[Ngee Ann Polytechnic]]\n| occupation = Actor, Host, Model\n| years_active = 2005-present\n| awards   = [[Star Search Singapore|Star Search]] 2007 : Champion\n| spouse = [[Kate Pang]]\n| children = Aden \u9648\u714a\u52bc <br> Avery \u9648\u8bed\u970f <ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.todayonline.com/entertainment/television/kate-pang-andie-chen-welcome-baby-boy |title= Kate Pang, Andie Chen welcome baby boy |last1= Seah |first1= May |last2= |first2= |date= 30 June 2014 |website= TODAYOnline |publisher= |accessdate= 4 July 2014}}</ref>\n| module = {{Infobox Chinese|child=yes\n| t = \u9673\u90a6\u92c6\n| s = \u9648\u90a6\u92c6\n| p = Ch\u00e9n B\u0101ngj\u016bn\n}}\n}}\n'''Andie Chen''' ({{zh|t=\u9673\u90a6\u92c6 |s=\u9648\u90a6\u92c6|p=Ch\u00e9n B\u0101ng J\u016bn}}) is a Singaporean actor, host and vlogger. He was prominently a full-time [[Mediacorp]] artiste from 2005 to 2017 but continues to film on an ad-hoc basis. On 1 November 2017, Chen announced that he will not be renewing his contract with Mediacorp. Chen left Medicorp on 31 October 2017 with his wife, [[Kate Pang]].\n\n==Career==\nChen's first appearance on television was in the [[Mediacorp Channel 5|Channel 5]] series ''[[Growing Up (Singaporean TV series)|Growing Up]]'' Season 2 Ep 12: Brother Of Mine in which he made a cameo flashback appearance as a child version of Tay Wee Seng, older brother of Lim Kay Tong\u2019s character Charlie Tay Wee Kiat\u2019s older brother and was credited as Andy Tan in year 1997.<ref>{{cite news|title=Andie Chen's special relationship with Romeo Tan|url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/entertainmentfeatures/view/1132769/1/.html|publisher=[[Channel News Asia]]|date=2 June 2011}}</ref> He shot to prominence after winning [[Star Search 2007]] and earned a contract with [[MediaCorp]].<ref>{{cite news|title=22-year-old Andie Chen wins Star Search 2007|url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/singaporelocalnews/view/309599/1/.html|publisher=[[Channel News Asia]]|date=4 November 2007}}</ref> He was given his first television roles the following year, most notably in the blockbuster period drama ''[[The Little Nyonya]]''. Since then he has starred in many  high-profile television dramas such as ''[[Unriddle]]'', ''[[C.L.I.F.]]'', ''[[Code of Honour]]'', ''[[Joys of Life]]'', ''[[The Journey (trilogy series)]]'' and [[The Lead (TV Series)|''The Lead'']].\n\nChen has made his stage debut in August 2015, taking up a lead role in the third staging of the popular Mandarin musical, ''December Rains'', by Toy Factory Productions. The musical, directed by Goh Boon Teck and written by renowned local songwriter [[Liang Wern Fook]], also stars Chriz Tong and Sugie Phua, with songs co-written by Liang and composer-singer [[Jimmy Ye Liang Jun|Jimmy Ye]].<ref>{{cite web|first1=May|last1=Seah|title=TV actor Andie Chen takes to the stage|url=http://www.todayonline.com/entertainment/arts/tv-actor-andie-chen-takes-stage?singlepage=true|website=[[Today (Singapore newspaper)|Today]]|accessdate=2015-04-28|date=27 April 2015}}</ref>\n\nChen was nominated for 3 categories at [[Star Awards 2017]], which are [[Star Awards for Best Actor|Best Actor]] for [[If Only I Could (TV series)|If Only I Could]], [[Star Awards for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]] for [[Hero (2016 TV series)|Hero]] & [[Star Awards for Top 10 Most Popular Male Artistes|Top 10 Most Popular Male Artistes]]. On 1 November 2017, Chen announced that he will not be renewing his contract with Mediacorp. Chen left Medicorp on 31 October 2017 with his wife, [[Kate Pang]]. His last drama series with Mediacorp was  ''[[The Lead (TV Series)|The Lead]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/lifestyle/andie-chen-and-kate-pang-leave-mediacorp-9363318|title=Celebrity couple Andie Chen and Kate Pang say goodbye to Mediacorp|work=Channel NewsAsia|access-date=2017-11-02|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/lifestyle/entertainment/andie-chen-and-kate-pang-leave-mediacorp|title=Celebrity couple Andie Chen and Kate Pang leave Mediacorp|last=hermesauto|date=2017-11-01|work=The Straits Times|access-date=2017-11-02|language=en}}</ref> He was nominated for [[Top 10 Most Popular Male Artistes]] at the Star Awards 2018.\n\n==Personal life==\n\nChen graduated from [[Tanglin Secondary School]] before he proceeded on to [[Ngee Ann Polytechnic]] in which he obtained a diploma in Film, Sound and Video.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://entertainment.xin.msn.com/en/celebrity/bios/Andie-Chen.aspx |title=Archived copy |access-date=2012-07-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120525155847/http://entertainment.xin.msn.com/en/celebrity/bios/Andie-Chen.aspx |archive-date=2012-05-25 |url-status=dead }}</ref> He married actress [[Kate Pang]] in 2013 after a secret courtship and they have a son Aden (born 30 June 2014) and a daughter Avery (born 16 June 2016).<ref>{{cite news|title=Kate Pang makes TV comeback, though drama serials are on the backburner for now|url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/entertainment/kate-pang-makes-tv/1703354.html|publisher=[[Channel NewsAsia]]|date=9 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Andie Chen, Kate Pang welcome baby daughter|url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/andie-chen-kate-pang/2877588.html|publisher=[[Channel NewsAsia]]|date=16 June 2016}}</ref> Chen and Pang has a parenting channel named Kandie Family which was launched in 2016.<ref>https://www.kandienetwork.com/about/{{Dead link|date=August 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n===Television/Webisodes===\n====English Series====\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Work !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | '''2009''' || ''[[Fighting Spiders]]'' || Tony Lee || \n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | '''2010''' || ''Fighting Spiders II'' || Tony Lee || \n|-\n| ''[[The Pupil (TV series)|The Pupil]]'' || Andy || Episode: Blog Out\n|-\n| '''2017''' || ''[[Lion Mums 2|Lion Mums (Season 2)]]'' || rowspan=\"2\" |  Chong Meng || rowspan=\"2\" | \n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | '''2019''' || ''[[Lion Mums 3|Lion Mums (Season 3)]]'' \n|-\n|}\n\n====Chinese Series====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Work !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | '''2019'''|| ''The Good Fight'' \u81f4\u80dc\u51fa\u51fb || Zheng Bin \u8c22\u6b63\u658c ||\n|-\n|''The Driver '' \u4f3a\u673a ||  Reagen ||\n|-\n| ''My Agent Is A Hero 2'' \u6d41\u6d6a\u7ecf\u7eaa2 || Max ||\n|-\n|''Walk With Me'' \u8c22\u8c22\u4f60\u51fa\u73b0\u5728\u6211\u7684\u884c\u7a0b\u91cc || Wu Weikang \u4f0d\u4f1f\u5eb7||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | '''2018'''|| ''Love At Cavenagh Bridge'' \u52a0\u6587\u7eb3\u6865\u7684\u7ea6\u5b9a || Xiao Shaocong \u8427\u5c11\u806a || \n|-\n| ''My Agent Is A Hero'' \u6d41\u6d6a\u7ecf\u7eaa || Max ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | '''2017''' || ''[[The Lead (TV Series)|The Lead]]'' \u7b2c\u4e00\u4e3b\u89d2 || Hong Deping \u6d2a\u5fb7\u5e73 ||\n|-\n| ''K.O.'' || Latte Wang \u738b\u5b50\u806a ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | '''2016''' || ''[[Hero (2016 TV series)|Hero]]'' \u5927\u82f1\u96c4 || Ou Jinguang \u533a\u91d1\u5149 || \n|-\n| ''Trapped Minds'' \u5fc3\u9b54 || Haolin \u6d69\u6797 ||\n|-\n| ''[[If Only I Could (TV series)|If Only I Could]]''  \u5341\u5e74 ... \u4f60\u8fd8\u597d\u5417? || He Daxian \u4f55\u5927\u5148 || \n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | '''2015''' || ''Accidental Agents'' \u7edd\u961f\u4fdd\u9669 || Johnny ||\n|-\n| ''[[The Journey: Our Homeland]]'' \u4fe1\u7ea6\uff1a\u6211\u4eec\u7684\u5bb6\u56ed || Hong Dangyong \u6d2a\u5f53\u52c7 ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | '''2014''' || ''[[The Journey: Tumultuous Times]]'' \u4fe1\u7ea6\uff1a\u52a8\u8361\u7684\u5e74\u4ee3 || Hong Dangyong \u6d2a\u5f53\u52c7 ||\n|-\n|''[[Independent Heroes]]'' \u5ec9\u653f\u82f1\u96c4 || Jian Shaoxiong \u7b80\u5c11\u96c4 ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | '''2013''' || ''[[Disclosed]]'' \u63ed\u79d8 || Zhang Letian \u5f20\u4e50\u5929 ||\n|-\n| ''Break Free'' \u66d9\u5149 || Xu Haolong \u5f90\u6d69\u9f99 || \n|-\n| ''[[C.L.I.F. 2]]'' \u8b66\u5fbd\u5929\u804c 2 || Zhao Guohuang \u8d75\u56fd\u714c ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | '''2012''' || ''[[Joys of Life]]'' \u82b1\u6837\u4eba\u95f4 || Sun Zibin \u5b59\u5b50\u658c ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | '''2011''' || ''[[Code of Honour]]'' \u6b63\u4e49\u6b66\u9986 || Ou Jianfeng \u6b27\u5251\u950b ||\n|-\n| ''[[C.L.I.F.]]'' \u8b66\u5fbd\u5929\u804c || Zhao Guohuang \u8d75\u56fd\u714c ||\n|-\n| ''[[Prosperity (Singaporean TV series)|Prosperity]]'' \u559c\u4e8b\u5e74\u5e74 || Ma Yongjie \u9a6c\u6c38\u6377 ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|'''2010''' || ''[[Precious Babes]]'' \u4e09\u4e2a\u5973\u4eba\u4e00\u4e2a\u5b9d || Fu Weide \u5085\u709c\u5fb7 ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[Unriddle]]'' \u6700\u706b\u642d\u6863 || Yan Dewei \u4e25\u5fb7\u5a01 || rowspan=\"2\"|\n|-\n| Cai Zhiyong \u8521\u5fd7\u52c7 \n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | '''2009''' || ''Mr & Mrs Kok'' \u795e\u63a2\u5999\u592b\u59bb ||||\n|-\n| ''[[Friends Forever (TV series)|Friends Forever]]'' \u6211\u7231\u9ebb\u7ccd || Jeff \u77f3\u5065\u660e || \n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | '''2008''' || ''[[The Little Nyonya]]'' \u5c0f\u5a18\u60f9 || Alexandre Huang Tianbao \u9ec4\u5929\u5b9d || \n|-\n| ''[[The Defining Moment (2008 TV series)|The Defining Moment]]  '' \u6cb8\u817e\u51b0\u70b9 || Lin Kexi \u6797\u53ef\u559c ||\n|-\n|}\n\n===Films/Movies===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Work !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | '''2019''' || ''When Ghost Meet Zombie''<br> \u5973\u9b3c\u7231\u4e0a\u5c38 || ||\n*Pairs up with [[Kate Pang]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | '''2018''' || ''[[Oh! Squints III]]'' || Tommy \"Squints\" Palledorous ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | '''2013''' || ''[[Oh! Squints II]]'' || Tommy \"Squints\" Palledorous ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | '''2011''' || ''[[Already Famous (film)|Already Famous]]'' <br> \u4e00\u6ce1\u800c\u7ea2 || DW's Father <br> DW \u7236 ||\n*Pairs up with Tan Zhonglin\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | '''2007''' || ''[[Oh! Squints]]'' || Tommy \"Squints\" Palledorous ||\n|-\n|}\n\n== Theater ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:500px\"\n|-\n! width=10|Year\n! Title\n! Role\n|-\n| 2015 || ''December Rains'' \u96e8\u5b63 || Zhou Ying Xiong \u5468\u82f1\u96c4\n|}\n\n==Accolades==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! Year !! Ceremony !! Award !! Nominated Work !! Result\n|-\n| '''2007''' \n| [[Star Search (Singapore season 9)|Star Search (Season 9)]] \n|  Champion \n| {{N/A}} \n| {{won}}\n|-\n| '''2009'''\n| [[Star Awards 2009|15th Star Awards Ceremony]]\n| [[Star Awards for Best Newcomer|Best Newcomer]]  \n| {{N/A}}  \n| {{Nom}} \n|-\n| '''2011'''\n| [[Star Awards 2011|17th Star Awards Ceremony]]\n| [[Star Awards for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]]  \n| ''[[Precious Babes]]'' <br> {{small|(as Fu Weide)}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| '''2012''' \n| [[Star Awards 2012|18th Star Awards Ceremony]]\n| [[Star Awards for Best Actor|Best Actor]] \n| ''[[Code of Honour]]'' <br> {{small|(as Ou Jianfeng)}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| '''2016''' \n| [[Star Awards 2016|22nd Star Awards Ceremony]]\n| [[Star Awards for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]] \n| ''[[The Journey: Our Homeland]]'' <br> {{small|(as Hong Dangyong)}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n |rowspan=\"3\"| '''2017''' \n| rowspan=\"3\"| [[Star Awards 2017|23rd Star Awards Ceremony]]\n| [[Star Awards for Best Actor|Best Actor]] \n| ''[[If Only I Could (TV series)|If Only I Could]]'' <br> {{small|(as He Daxian)}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Star Awards for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]] \n| ''[[Hero (2016 TV series)|Hero]]'' <br> {{small|(as Ou Jinguang)}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Star Awards for Top 10 Most Popular Male Artistes|Top 10 Most Popular Male Artistes]]\n| {{N/A}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| '''2018'''\n| [[Star Awards 2018|24th Star Awards Ceremony]]\n| [[Star Awards for Top 10 Most Popular Male Artistes|Top 10 Most Popular Male Artistes]]\n| ''[[The Lead]]'' <br> {{small|(as Hong Deping)}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| '''2019'''\n| [[Star Awards 2019|25th Star Awards Ceremony]]\n| [[Star Awards for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]] \n| ''My Agent Is A Hero'' <br> {{small|(as Max)}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| '''2019''' || [[Star Awards 2019|25th Star Awards Ceremony]] || [[Star Awards for Top 10 Most Popular Male Artistes|Top 10 Most Popular Male Artistes]] || {{N/A}} || {{nom}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n<!-- Per [[WP:ELMINOFFICIAL]], choose one official website only -->\n* {{facebook|andiechen}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Chen, Andie}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Singaporean male television actors]]\n[[Category:Ngee Ann Polytechnic alumni]]\n[[Category:Singaporean people of Chinese descent]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Singaporean actor, host and vlogger|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{infobox person\n| name = Andie Chen\n| image = \n| alt = \n| caption = \n| birth_name = Andy Tan Bang Jun\n| birth_date = \n| birth_place = [[Singapore]]\n| residence = [[Singapore]]\n| nationality = [[Singaporean]]\n| education = [[Tanglin Secondary School]] \n| alma_mater = [[Ngee Ann Polytechnic]]\n| occupation = Actor, Host, Model\n| years_active = 2005-present\n| awards   = [[Star Search Singapore|Star Search]] 2007 : Champion\n| spouse = [[Kate Pang]]\n| children = Aden \u9648\u714a\u52bc <br> Avery \u9648\u8bed\u970f <ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.todayonline.com/entertainment/television/kate-pang-andie-chen-welcome-baby-boy |title= Kate Pang, Andie Chen welcome baby boy |last1= Seah |first1= May |last2= |first2= |date= 30 June 2014 |website= TODAYOnline |publisher= |accessdate= 4 July 2014}}</ref>\n| module = {{Infobox Chinese|child=yes\n| t = \u9673\u90a6\u92c6\n| s = \u9648\u90a6\u92c6\n| p = Ch\u00e9n B\u0101ngj\u016bn\n}}\n}}\n'''Andie Chen''' ({{zh|t=\u9673\u90a6\u92c6 |s=\u9648\u90a6\u92c6|p=Ch\u00e9n B\u0101ng J\u016bn}}) is a Singaporean actor, host and vlogger. He was prominently a full-time [[Mediacorp]] artiste from 2005 to 2017 but continues to film on an ad-hoc basis. On 1 November 2017, Chen announced that he will not be renewing his contract with Mediacorp. Chen left Medicorp on 31 October 2017 with his wife , [[Kate Pang]].\n\n==Career==\nChen's first appearance on television was in the [[Mediacorp Channel 5|Channel 5]] series ''[[Growing Up (Singaporean TV series)|Growing Up]]'' Season 2 Ep 12: Brother Of Mine in which he made a cameo flashback appearance as a child version of Tay Wee Seng, older brother of Lim Kay Tong\u2019s character Charlie Tay Wee Kiat\u2019s older brother and was credited as Andy Tan in year 1997.<ref>{{cite news|title=Andie Chen's special relationship with Romeo Tan|url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/entertainmentfeatures/view/1132769/1/.html|publisher=[[Channel News Asia]]|date=2 June 2011}}</ref> He shot to prominence after winning [[Star Search 2007]] and earned a contract with [[MediaCorp]].<ref>{{cite news|title=22-year-old Andie Chen wins Star Search 2007|url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/singaporelocalnews/view/309599/1/.html|publisher=[[Channel News Asia]]|date=4 November 2007}}</ref> He was given his first television roles the following year, most notably in the blockbuster period drama ''[[The Little Nyonya]]''. Since then he has starred in many  high-profile television dramas such as ''[[Unriddle]]'', ''[[C.L.I.F.]]'', ''[[Code of Honour]]'', ''[[Joys of Life]]'', ''[[The Journey (trilogy series)]]'' and [[The Lead (TV Series)|''The Lead'']].\n\nChen has made his stage debut in August 2015, taking up a lead role in the third staging of the popular Mandarin musical, ''December Rains'', by Toy Factory Productions. The musical, directed by Goh Boon Teck and written by renowned local songwriter [[Liang Wern Fook]], also stars Chriz Tong and Sugie Phua, with songs co-written by Liang and composer-singer [[Jimmy Ye Liang Jun|Jimmy Ye]].<ref>{{cite web|first1=May|last1=Seah|title=TV actor Andie Chen takes to the stage|url=http://www.todayonline.com/entertainment/arts/tv-actor-andie-chen-takes-stage?singlepage=true|website=[[Today (Singapore newspaper)|Today]]|accessdate=2015-04-28|date=27 April 2015}}</ref>\n\nChen was nominated for 3 categories at [[Star Awards 2017]], which are [[Star Awards for Best Actor|Best Actor]] for [[If Only I Could (TV series)|If Only I Could]], [[Star Awards for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]] for [[Hero (2016 TV series)|Hero]] & [[Star Awards for Top 10 Most Popular Male Artistes|Top 10 Most Popular Male Artistes]]. On 1 November 2017, Chen announced that he will not be renewing his contract with Mediacorp. Chen left Medicorp on 31 October 2017 with his wife , [[Kate Pang]]. His last drama series with Mediacorp was  ''[[The Lead (TV Series)|The Lead]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/lifestyle/andie-chen-and-kate-pang-leave-mediacorp-9363318|title=Celebrity couple Andie Chen and Kate Pang say goodbye to Mediacorp|work=Channel NewsAsia|access-date=2017-11-02|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/lifestyle/entertainment/andie-chen-and-kate-pang-leave-mediacorp|title=Celebrity couple Andie Chen and Kate Pang leave Mediacorp|last=hermesauto|date=2017-11-01|work=The Straits Times|access-date=2017-11-02|language=en}}</ref> He was nominated for [[Top 10 Most Popular Male Artistes]] at the Star Awards 2018.\n\n==Personal life==\n\nChen graduated from [[Tanglin Secondary School]] before he proceeded on to [[Ngee Ann Polytechnic]] in which he obtained a diploma in Film, Sound and Video.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://entertainment.xin.msn.com/en/celebrity/bios/Andie-Chen.aspx |title=Archived copy |access-date=2012-07-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120525155847/http://entertainment.xin.msn.com/en/celebrity/bios/Andie-Chen.aspx |archive-date=2012-05-25 |url-status=dead }}</ref> He married actress [[Kate Pang]] in 2013 after a secret courtship and they have a son Aden (born June 30, 2014) and a daughter Avery (born June 16, 2016).<ref>{{cite news|title=Kate Pang makes TV comeback, though drama serials are on the backburner for now|url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/entertainment/kate-pang-makes-tv/1703354.html|publisher=[[Channel NewsAsia]]|date=9 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Andie Chen, Kate Pang welcome baby daughter|url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/andie-chen-kate-pang/2877588.html|publisher=[[Channel NewsAsia]]|date=16 June 2016}}</ref> Chen and Pang has a parenting channel named Kandie Family which was launched in 2016.<ref>https://www.kandienetwork.com/about/{{Dead link|date=August 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n===Television/Webisodes===\n====English Series====\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Work !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | '''2009''' || ''[[Fighting Spiders]]'' || Tony Lee || \n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | '''2010''' || ''Fighting Spiders II'' || Tony Lee || \n|-\n| ''[[The Pupil (TV series)|The Pupil]]'' || Andy || Episode: Blog Out\n|-\n| '''2017''' || ''[[Lion Mums 2|Lion Mums (Season 2)]]'' || rowspan=\"2\" |  Chong Meng || rowspan=\"2\" | \n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | '''2019''' || ''[[Lion Mums 3|Lion Mums (Season 3)]]'' \n|-\n|}\n\n====Chinese Series====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Work !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | '''2019'''|| ''The Good Fight'' \u81f4\u80dc\u51fa\u51fb || Zheng Bin \u8c22\u6b63\u658c ||\n|-\n|''The Driver '' \u4f3a\u673a ||  Reagen ||\n|-\n| ''My Agent Is A Hero 2'' \u6d41\u6d6a\u7ecf\u7eaa2 || Max ||\n|-\n|''Walk With Me'' \u8c22\u8