      = \n| pattern_ra1        = \n| pattern_sh1        = \n| pattern_so1        = \n| leftarm1           = \n| body1              = \n| rightarm1          = \n| shorts1            = \n| socks1             = \n| pattern_la2        = \n| pattern_b2         = \n| pattern_ra2        = \n| pattern_sh2        = \n| pattern_so2        = \n| leftarm2           = \n| body2              = \n| rightarm2          = \n| shorts2            = \n| socks2             = \n| pattern_la3        = \n| pattern_b3         = \n| pattern_ra3        = \n| pattern_sh3        = \n| pattern_so3        = \n| leftarm3           = \n| body3              = \n| rightarm3          = \n| shorts3            = \n| socks3             = \n| prevseason         = \n| nextseason         = \n}}\n\nThe '''2019\u201320 [[Chittagong Abahani]] season''' is the club's<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/teams/bangladesh/chittagong-abahani/8275/|title=Bangladesh - Abahani Limited Chittagong - Results, fixtures, squad, statistics, photos, videos and news - Soccerway|website=int.soccerway.com|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref> 40th season since its establishment in 1980<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://chattogram24.com/news-view/1167/\u099a\u099f\u09cd\u099f\u0997\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09ae-\u0986\u09ac\u09be\u09b9\u09a8\u09c0\u2019\u09b0-\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a4\u09bf\u09b7\u09cd\u09a0\u09be\u09ac\u09be\u09b0\u09cd\u09b7\u09bf\u0995\u09c0-\u0989\u09a6\u09af\u09be\u09aa\u09a8-|title=\u099a\u099f\u09cd\u099f\u0997\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09ae \u0986\u09ac\u09be\u09b9\u09a8\u09c0\u2019\u09b0 \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a4\u09bf\u09b7\u09cd\u09a0\u09be\u09ac\u09be\u09b0\u09cd\u09b7\u09bf\u0995\u09c0 \u0989\u09a6\u09af\u09be\u09aa\u09a8|last=Ltd|first=Muktodhara Tech|website=chattogram24.com|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref> and their 10th season in the [[Bangladesh Football Premier League|Bangladesh Premier League]]. This also remarks their sixth consecutive season in the top flight after getting promoted in 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/uncategorized/2013/06/09/ctg-abahani-wins-bcl-title|title=Ctg Abahani wins BCL title|date=2013-06-09|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref>\n\n==Summary==\n===Pre-season===\nOn October 2019, [[Abahani Limited (Chittagong)|Chittagong Abahani]] organized and participated in [[2019 Sheikh Kamal International Club Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/bangla/%E0%A6%96%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B2%E0%A6%BE/%E0%A6%B6%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%96-%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AE%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B2-%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%9C%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A4%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%95-%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B2%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AC-%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AA%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%9A%E0%A7%8B%E0%A6%96-%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%96%E0%A6%AC%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%A8-%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A6%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%93%E0%A6%AA%E0%A6%B0-123571|title=\u09b6\u09c7\u0996 \u0995\u09be\u09ae\u09be\u09b2 \u0986\u09a8\u09cd\u09a4\u09b0\u09cd\u099c\u09be\u09a4\u09bf\u0995 \u0995\u09cd\u09b2\u09be\u09ac \u0995\u09be\u09aa\u09c7 \u099a\u09cb\u0996 \u09b0\u09be\u0996\u09ac\u09c7\u09a8 \u09af\u09be\u09a6\u09c7\u09b0 \u0993\u09aa\u09b0|date=2019-10-19|website=The Daily Star Bangla|language=bn|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bangla.bdnews24.com/sport/article1674929.bdnews|title=\u09b6\u09c7\u0996 \u0995\u09be\u09ae\u09be\u09b2 \u0995\u09cd\u09b2\u09be\u09ac \u0995\u09be\u09aa\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ee \u09a6\u09b2 \u099a\u09c2\u09a1\u09bc\u09be\u09a8\u09cd\u09a4|last=\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a4\u09bf\u09ac\u09c7\u09a6\u0995|first=\u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09c0\u09a1\u09bc\u09be|last2=\u09a1\u099f\u0995\u09ae|first2=\u09ac\u09bf\u09a1\u09bf\u09a8\u09bf\u0989\u099c \u099f\u09cb\u09af\u09bc\u09c7\u09a8\u09cd\u099f\u09bf\u09ab\u09cb\u09b0|website=bangla.bdnews24.com|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> Players including [[Bangladesh national football team|Bangladesh National Football Team]] captain [[Jamal Bhuyan]], [[2010 FIFA World Cup]] Quarterfinalist [[Prince Tagoe]], [[Luka Rotkovi\u0107|Luka Rotkovic]], [[Petar Plani\u0107]] were signed for the tournament.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://footballghana.com/ex-black-stars-striker-prince-tagoe-secures-move-to-bangladeshi-side-chittagong-abahani|title=Ex-Black Stars striker Prince Tagoe secures move to Bangladeshi side Chittagong Abahani|date=2019-10-22|website=Footballghana|language=en-gb|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/prince-tagoe-joins-bangladeshi-side-chittagong-abahani|title=Prince Tagoe joins Bangladeshi side Chittagong Abahani|date=2019-10-22|website=GhanaSoccernet|language=en-gb|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/sport/2019/10/24/maruful-jamal-up-against-bagan-after-five-years|title=Maruful, Jamal up against Bagan after five years|date=2019-10-24|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> They also signed former National Team head coach [[Maruful Haque]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.somoynews.tv/pages/details/178450|script-title=bn:\u0986\u09a8\u09cd\u09a4\u09b0\u09cd\u099c\u09be\u09a4\u09bf\u0995 \u0995\u09cd\u09b2\u09be\u09ac \u0995\u09be\u09aa \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09b8\u09cd\u09a4\u09c1\u09a4\u09bf \u09b8\u09be\u09b0\u099b\u09c7 \u099a\u099f\u09cd\u099f\u0997\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09ae \u0986\u09ac\u09be\u09b9\u09a8\u09c0-\u09a2\u09be\u0995\u09be \u0986\u09ac\u09be\u09b9\u09a8\u09c0|work=Somoy News|language=bn|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> Chittagong Abahani started the tournament with a 4\u20131 win against Maldivian side [[TC Sports Club]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/sport/2019/10/19/ctg-abahani-off-to-flying-start|title=Ctg Abahani off to flying start|date=2019-10-19|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.prothomalo.com/sports/news/203555/Sk-Kamal-Football-Ctg-Abahani-crush-Maldives%E2%80%99-TC|title=Sk Kamal Football: Ctg Abahani crush Maldives\u2019 TC Sports 4\u20131|website=Prothom Alo|language=en|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> Abahani also beaten [[Young Elephants FC]] by 4\u20132<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/sport/2019/10/24/jamal-shines-as-ctg-abahani-win-again|title=Jamal shines as Ctg Abahani win again|date=2019-10-24|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> but lost with [[Mohun Bagan A.C.|Mohun Bagan]] by 1\u20130.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/sports/football/news/ctg-abahani-mohun-bagan-thru-1818760|title=Ctg Abahani, Mohun Bagan thru\u2019|date=2019-10-26|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> In semi-final, Abahani beaten [[Gokulam Kerala F.C.|Gokulam Kerala FC]] with an [[Added Extra Time|extra-time]] goal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportstar.thehindu.com/football/sheikh-kamal-cup-2019-gokulam-kerala-chittagong-abahani-semifinals-kisekka-marcus-joseph-indian-football/article29815923.ece|title=Sheikh Kamal Cup semifinals: Gokulam goes down in five-goal thriller|last=Sportstar|first=Team|website=Sportstar|language=en|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/sport/football/2019/10/28/ctg-abahani-seal-final-berth|title=CTG Abahani seal final berth|date=2019-10-28|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> However, Chittagong Abahani defeated by [[Terengganu FC]] in the Final<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/sport/football/2019/10/31/terengganu-down-ctg-abahani|title=Terengganu down Ctg Abahani|date=2019-10-31|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/sports/football/news/terengganu-beat-ctg-abahani-become-skicc-champs-1821340|title=Terengganu beat Ctg Abahani to become SKICC champs|date=2019-10-31|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> and finished the tournament as runners-up.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/sports/football/news/terengganu-stifle-ctg-abahanis-dream-1821544|title=Terengganu stifle Ctg Abahani\u2019s dream|date=2019-11-01|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> [[Luka Rotkovi\u0107|Luka]], who scored three goals, was top scorer for Abahani in the tournament. The players who joined the team on loan and foreigners except Ikbol, Didier and Matthew were released after the tournament.\n\nOn November 20, Abahani signed an one-year contract with [[Maruful Haque]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.prothomalo.com/sports/article/1625292/%E0%A6%AD%E0%A6%BE%E0%A7%9C%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%9F%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%A5%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%9A%E0%A6%9F%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%9F%E0%A6%97%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AE%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A5%E0%A6%BE%E0%A7%9F%E0%A7%80-%E0%A6%B9%E0%A6%9A%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%9B%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%A8-%E0%A6%AE%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%AB%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%B2|script-title=bn:\u09ad\u09be\u09a1\u09bc\u09be\u099f\u09c7 \u09a5\u09c7\u0995\u09c7 \u099a\u099f\u09cd\u099f\u0997\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09ae\u09c7 \u09b8\u09cd\u09a5\u09be\u09af\u09bc\u09c0 \u09b9\u099a\u09cd\u099b\u09c7\u09a8 \u09ae\u09be\u09b0\u09c1\u09ab\u09c1\u09b2|date=2019-11-20|work=Prothom Alo|language=bn|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.jagonews24.com/sports/football/539191|script-title=bn:\u0986\u09b0\u09be\u09ae\u09ac\u09be\u0997 \u099b\u09c7\u09a1\u09bc\u09c7 \u099a\u099f\u09cd\u099f\u0997\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09ae \u0986\u09ac\u09be\u09b9\u09a8\u09c0\u09b0 \u0995\u09cb\u099a \u09b9\u099a\u09cd\u099b\u09c7\u09a8 \u09ae\u09be\u09b0\u09c1\u09ab\u09c1\u09b2 \u09b9\u0995|work=Jago News 24|language=bn|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dailynayadiganta.com/football/457764/|script-title=bn:\u09aa\u09be\u09b0\u09bf\u09b6\u09cd\u09b0\u09ae\u09bf\u0995\u09c7\u09b0 \u09b0\u09c7\u0995\u09b0\u09cd\u09a1 \u0995\u09cb\u099a \u09ae\u09be\u09b0\u09c1\u09ab\u09c1\u09b2\u09c7\u09b0!|date=1970-01-01|work=Daily Nayadiganta|language=bn|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> The signing made record as Maruful became highest paid local head coach of that season.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.banglatribune.com/sport/news/600758/%E0%A7%AD%E0%A7%A6-%E0%A6%B2%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%96%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%AE%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%AB%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%B2-%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%93-%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AE%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%B6%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%80|script-title=bn:\u09ed\u09e6 \u09b2\u09be\u0996\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ae\u09be\u09b0\u09c1\u09ab\u09c1\u09b2 \u0986\u09b0\u0993 \u0986\u09a4\u09cd\u09ae\u09ac\u09bf\u09b6\u09cd\u09ac\u09be\u09b8\u09c0 |website=Bangla Tribune|language=bn|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> [[Brazilians|Brazilian]] footballer [[Nixon Guylherme]] and [[Uzbekistan|Uzbek]] defender Shukurali Pulatov were signed to fill up foreign quota while [[Bangladesh national football team|Bangladesh]] international [[Nasirul Islam Nasir]], [[Monjurur Rahman Manik]], Rakib Hossain, Mohammad Rocky etc. were also signed to form a strong squad for upcoming season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/sport/2019/11/21/ctg-abahani-confident-with-maruful-as-coach|title=Ctg Abahani confident with Maruful as coach|date=2019-11-21|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref>\n\nFrom December 4 to December 8, [[Abahani Limited (Chittagong)|Chittagong Abahani]] took part in ''Mymensingh DFA Challenge Cup'', a [[pre-season]] tournament, along with [[Saif SC|Saif Sporting Club]] and [[Bangladesh Police FC]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.prothomalo.com/sports/article/1627045/%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%A8-%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%9B%E0%A7%81-%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%B8%E0%A6%9B%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%A6%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B6%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%AB%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%9F%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%B2%E0%A7%87|title=\u09a8\u09a4\u09c1\u09a8 \u0995\u09bf\u099b\u09c1 \u0986\u09b8\u099b\u09c7 \u09a6\u09c7\u09b6\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ab\u09c1\u099f\u09ac\u09b2\u09c7|date=2019-11-30|website=\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a5\u09ae \u0986\u09b2\u09cb|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> The tournament was won by defeating [[Bangladesh Police FC|Police FC]] in final with 1\u20130 margin.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.durjoybangla.com/%E0%A6%AE%E0%A7%9F%E0%A6%AE%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%B8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%82%E0%A6%B9%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%A1%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%8F%E0%A6%AB%E0%A6%8F-%E0%A6%9A%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B2%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%9E%E0%A7%8D/|title=\u09ae\u09af\u09bc\u09ae\u09a8\u09b8\u09bf\u0982\u09b9\u09c7 \u09a1\u09bf\u098f\u09ab\u098f \u099a\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u09b2\u09c7\u099e\u09cd\u099c \u0995\u09be\u09aa \u09ab\u09c1\u099f\u09ac\u09b2 \u099f\u09c1\u09b0\u09cd\u09a8\u09be\u09ae\u09c7\u09a8\u09cd\u099f\u09c7 \u09ab\u09be\u0987\u09a8\u09be\u09b2\u09c7 \u09e7-\u09e6 \u0997\u09cb\u09b2\u09c7 \u099a\u099f\u09cd\u099f\u0997\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09ae \u0986\u09ac\u09be\u09b9\u09a8\u09c0 \u099c\u09af\u09bc\u09c0 -durjoy bangla {{!}} \u09a6\u09c1\u09b0\u09cd\u099c\u09af\u09bc \u09ac\u09be\u0982\u09b2\u09be|website=durjoybangla.com|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.satv.tv/%e0%a6%a1%e0%a6%bf%e0%a6%8f%e0%a6%ab%e0%a6%8f-%e0%a6%9a%e0%a7%8d%e0%a6%af%e0%a6%be%e0%a6%b2%e0%a7%87%e0%a6%9e%e0%a7%8d%e0%a6%9c-%e0%a6%95%e0%a6%be%e0%a6%aa-%e0%a6%ab%e0%a7%81%e0%a6%9f%e0%a6%ac/|title=\u09a1\u09bf\u098f\u09ab\u098f \u099a\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u09b2\u09c7\u099e\u09cd\u099c \u0995\u09be\u09aa \u09ab\u09c1\u099f\u09ac\u09b2 \u099f\u09c1\u09b0\u09cd\u09a8\u09be\u09ae\u09c7\u09a8\u09cd\u099f\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ab\u09be\u0987\u09a8\u09be\u09b2 \u0996\u09c7\u09b2\u09be \u0985\u09a8\u09c1\u09b7\u09cd\u09a0\u09bf\u09a4 {{!}} SATV|language=bn-BD|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref>\n\n===December===\nIn this month, the new football season started with [[2019\u201320 Bangladesh Federation Cup|2019 Federation cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/sport/2019/12/17/football-season-kicks-off-with-fed-cup-wednesday|title=Football season kicks off with Fed Cup Wednesday|date=2019-12-17|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> [[Abahani Limited (Chittagong)|Abahani]] played first match of the season against [[Brothers Union|Brother Union]] in 22 December and won it by 2\u20130 with goals scored by [[Nixon Guylherme|Nixon]] and Matthew.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/sports/football/news/ctg-abahani-last-8-1843789|title=Ctg Abahani in last 8|date=2019-12-23|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://unb.com.bd/category/Sports/fed-cup-football-ctg-abahani-eliminate-brothers-union/39006|title=Fed Cup Football: Ctg Abahani eliminate Brothers Union|work=UNB|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> Five days later, the last match of Group B against [[Bashundhara Kings|Bashundhara kings]] was won with 2\u20130 score.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://unb.com.bd/category/Sports/fed-cup-ctg-abahani-outclass-kings-2-0/39498|title=Fed Cup: Ctg Abahani outclass Kings 2\u20130|work=UNB|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> Rakib and Didier scored the goals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.daily-sun.com/post/449710/Fed-Cup:-Ctg-Abahani-outclass-Kings-20|title=Fed Cup: Ctg Abahani outclass Kings 2\u20130|website=Daily Sun|language=en|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> Abahani qualified for the knockout stage as group champion.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/94856/chittagong-abahani-emerge-group-b-champ|title=Chittagong Abahani emerge Group B champ|website=New Age |access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> Three days later, Abahani suffered a 2\u20130 defeat against [[Dhaka Mohammedan]]<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://unb.com.bd/category/Sports/fed-cup-dhaka-mohammedan-reach-semifinal-eliminating-ctg-abahani/39788|title=Fed Cup: Dhaka Mohammedan reach semifinal eliminating Ctg...|work=UNB|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> in quarter-final and were knocked out from 2019 Federation Cup.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/sport/football/2019/12/30/msc-outplay-ctg-abahani-to-reach-semis|title=MSC outplay CTG Abahani to reach semis|date=2019-12-30|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref>\n\n===January===\nThe club started the new year with good news as two players from the team, Manik Hossain Mollah, [[Monjurur Rahman Manik]] and [[Rakib Hossain]] called up in 23-men squad of [[Bangladesh national football team|Bangladesh National Team]] for [[2020 Bangabandhu Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/sport/football/2020/01/06/manik-gets-a-call-up-for-bangabandhu-gold-cup|title=Manik gets a call-up for Bangabandhu Gold Cup|date=2020-01-06|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.theindependentbd.com/home/printnews/231069|title=23-member team announced for Bangabandhu Gold Cup |work=The Independent |location=Dhaka |access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref>  Rakib and Manik both made their international debut against [[Sri Lanka national football team|Sri Lanka]]. \n\n===February===\nCtg Abahani started [[2019\u201320 Bangladesh Premier League (football)|2019-20 BPL]] against [[Sheikh Jamal Dhanmondi Club|Sheikh Jamal DC]] on 13th February. The away match was won with 2\u20130 as [[Kpehi Didier Brossou|Didier]] and [[Matthew Chinedu|Matthew]] found the net.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/sport/2020/02/14/ctg-abahani-outplay-sk-jamal|title=Ctg Abahani outplay Sk Jamal|date=2020-02-14|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref> Five days later, the team suffered a 2\u20131 defeat against [[Arambagh KS]] in the first home game of the league. [[Shakhawat Hossain Rony|Shakhawat Rony]] scored the only goal in that match. On 23rd February, Ctg Abahani played a 2-2 draw with [[Saif SC]] at [[Mymensingh Stadium|Mymensingh]] conceding two late goals. [[Nixon Guylherme|Nixon]] & [[Matthew Chinedu|Matthew]] scored in that match. Mohammad Nayeem made his debut for the team in this match.\n\n===March===\nCtg Abahani played their second home game of the league against [[Sheikh Russel KC]] on 2nd March. The match was won by 2-0 Nixon & Mannaf Rabby scored. Five days later, Ctg Abahani defeated defending runners-up [[Dhaka Abahani]] by 2-0 on away schedule. Didier & Nasirul found the net on the game. On 15th March, they faced defending champion [[Bashundhara Kings]] at Nilphamari. Ctg Abahani made a historic comeback from 3-0 to 3-4 & won the match. [[Nixon Guylherme|Nixon]] netted a brace when [[Kpehi Didier Brossou|Didier]] & [[Matthew Chinedu|Matthew]] each scored one goal. Mannaf Rabby provided two assists. On 16th March, remaining matches of month postponed till 31st march due to [[Coronavirus outbreak 2020|coronavirus outbreak]].      \n===April===\n===May===\n===June===  \n\n==Players==\n'''Chittagong Abahani Ltd.''' squad for 2019\u201320 season.\n{{updated|25 November 2019}}\n\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=1|nat=Bangladesh|pos=GK|name=[[Mohammad Nehal]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=2|nat=Bangladesh|pos=DF|name=Mohammad Rockey}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=3|nat=Bangladesh|pos=DF|name=Shawkat Russel}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=4|nat=Bangladesh|pos=MF|name=[[Manik Hossain Molla]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=5|nat=Bangladesh|pos=DF|name=[[Monjurur Rahman Manik]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=6|nat=Bangladesh|pos=DF|name=[[Nasirul Islam Nasir]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=7|nat=Bangladesh|pos=MF|name=[[Rakib Hossain]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=[[Captain (association football)|Captain]]|no=8|nat=Ivory Coast|pos=MF|name=[[Kpehi Didier Brossou]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=9|nat=Brazil|pos=FW|name=[[Nixon Guylherme]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=10|nat=Nigeria|pos=MF|name=[[Matthew Chinedu]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=11|nat=Bangladesh|pos=MF|name=Mohammad Shohel Rana}}\n{{Fs player|other=[[Captain (association football)|3rd captain]]|no=12|nat=Bangladesh|pos=MF|name=Koushik Barua}}\n{{Fs player|other=[[Captain (association football)|2nd captain]]|no=14|nat=Bangladesh|pos=MF|name=[[Monaem Khan Raju]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=15|nat=Bangladesh|pos=MF|name=Shafiqul Islam}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=16|nat=Bangladesh|pos=MF|name=Saker Ullah}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=17|nat=Bangladesh|pos=MF|name=[[Mannaf Rabby]]}}\n{{Fs mid}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=18|nat=Bangladesh|pos=MF|name=Zahed Parvez Chowdhury}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=19|nat=Bangladesh|pos=MF|name=Kawsar Ali Rabbi}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=20|nat=Bangladesh|pos=FW|name=[[Shakhawat Hossain Rony]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=21|nat=Bangladesh|pos=DF|name=Ashik Ahammed}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=22|nat=Bangladesh|pos=GK|name=Azad Hossain}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=23|nat=Bangladesh|pos=DF|name=Monir Alam}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=24|nat=Uzbekistan|pos=DF|name=Ikbol Bobohonov}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=25|nat=Uzbekistan|pos=DF|name=[[Shukurali Pulatov]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=26|nat=Bangladesh|pos=DF|name=Saddam Hossain}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=28|nat=Bangladesh|pos=MF|name=Mynul Islam}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=30|nat=Bangladesh|pos=FW|name=Shakib Chowdhury}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=32|nat=Bangladesh|pos=DF|name=Rashed Hossain}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=33|nat=Bangladesh|pos=GK|name=Mohammad Nayeem}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=35|nat=Bangladesh|pos=DF|name=Apu Ahammad}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=40|nat=Bangladesh|pos=GK|name=Nasarul Islam}}\n{{Fs end}}\n----\n\n==Pre-season and friendlies==\n{{Football box collapsible\n|round = Friendly\n|id=|date=12 October 2019\n|time=\n|team1=[[Bangladesh Police FC]]\n|score=0\u20133\n|report=\n|team2=[[Chittagong Abahani]]\n|goals1=\n|goals2=\n* {{goal}} [[Matthew Chinedu|Matthew]]\n* {{goal}} Koushik \n* {{goal}} Rockey\n|location=Dhaka\n|stadium=APBN Ground\n|attendance=\n|referee=\n|result=W\n}}\n{{Football box collapsible\n|round = [[2019 Sheikh Kamal International Club Cup]]\n|id=|date=19 October 2019\n|time= \n|team1=[[Chittagong Abahani]]\n|score=4-1\n|report=https://www.dhakatribune.com/sport/2019/10/19/ctg-abahani-off-to-flying-start\n|team2=[[TC Sports Club]]\n|goals1=\n*[[Matthew Chinedu|Chinedu]] {{goal|8||39}}\n*Arafat {{goal|10}}\n*[[Luka Rotkovi\u0107|Rotkovi\u0107]] {{goal|71}}\n|goals2= *[[Ismail Easa|Easa]] {{goal|88}}\n|location=[[Chittagong]]\n|st